@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'KouQuad' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The gameplay is quite simple: click on a 'Quad', the coloured
tiles that are located in that Quad will rotate clockwise by one
position. If any coloured tile is moved next to a neighbouring tile
of the same colour, these tiles will be removed from the board,
leaving each tile empty, and you will get points according to the
number of removed tiles... Obviously, the more tiles of the same
colour(s) that are placed next to each other, the more points you
will get, as shown in the following table:

  2 tiles = 1 point
  3 tiles = 3 points
  4 tiles = 7 points
  5 tiles = 15 points
  etc.

  When it is no longer possible to place coloured tiles together,
click on the 'fall-and-move-left' button (located at the lower
right of the game board). It will move all remaining coloured tiles
together. This will give you another chance to place tiles of the
same colour together... but in doing so, it will give you no point.
The tiles will fall toward the bottom of the gameboard and all
fallen tiles, as well as piles of tiles, if there are 2 or more
that are piled up, will be moved toward the left side of the board.
All tiles of the same colour that are grouped together will be
removed. After that, if any tile remain, the game will be over.

  Continue the game until all coloured tiles are removed from the
game board. Then, the game continues and a new board will be
displayed...

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or press
the 'Esc' key.

